message: I blamed myself for what was happening. I would write to my family and say that everything was fine, that the city was beautiful. I never told my family about the situation, because I felt it was my fault.

data.description: This is one of three first-person accounts written by survivors of human trafficking. The others, as well as background about the project, can be found here. data.title: I Am a Survivor of Human Trafficking: Natalicia's Story
